<p>The United States announced it will withdraw roughly 700 troops from NATO’s borders with Ukraine, a move the administration says is part of a wider effort to shift resources toward the Indo-Pacific region . Officials gave few details about future cuts or timelines, prompting concern among European allies about a potential security vacuum on NATO’s eastern flank . The announcement marks the first public indication of the Trump administration’s plan to scale back some U.S. forces in Europe, even as military leaders emphasize the change is a repositioning rather than a severing of commitments .</p><img src='https://kagiproxy.com/img/iYMUonoP7FQPskJmyHsS_-btTUQUMNmjk0sEuqf7dVMmuECw552lIV-1j3HWF2VVnl5DozKqWhfdzk-bzaMDwLsOmdhxE12lGK_pu-ZvNoPFt_zHnbT7D4NxJHKiOpb634Cg5z6Qy9QPGqvqB7lKu_Sm4xVGJyV3L4fy8CCsQNXyyQJuXQHfco5keqVu2ELyOKh1waK5Fg' alt='U.S. troops taking part in a training exercise in Frecatei, Romania, in June.' /><br /><h3>Highlights:</h3><ul><li>Redeployment destination: U.S. units stationed in Romania are slated to be redeployed to Kentucky, according to military officials who described the move as a repositioning rather than a permanent removal .</li><li>Congressional backlash: Top Republican lawmakers who oversee Pentagon spending issued a rare joint criticism of the decision, saying they were not consulted and expressing concern about the implications for deterrence .</li><li>Pentagon response: U.S. military officials denied the withdrawals signal a reduced commitment to NATO, describing them as adjustments in force posture to address global priorities .</li><li>Policy milestone: Washington’s announcement represents the Trump administration’s first public plan to scale back forces in Europe, a notable shift in posture given the long-standing U.S. role in European security since World War II .</li></ul><h3>Perspectives:</h3><ul><li>U.S. administration: Officials described the withdrawals as part of a shift in resources to the Indo-Pacific to address growing strategic priorities in that region. (<a href='https://www.nytimes.com/2025/10/29/world/europe/us-troops-eastern-europe-romania.html'>The New York Times</a>)</li><li>European allies: Some NATO members warned the move could create a security vacuum along the alliance&#x27;s eastern border with Ukraine and expressed worries about deterrence. (<a href='https://japantoday.com/category/world/the-us-draws-down-troops-on-nato%27s-eastern-flank-as-europe-frets-about-a-security-vacuum'>Japan Today</a>)</li><li>Top Republican lawmakers: Senior Republican leaders who oversee Pentagon oversight criticized the decision and said they were not consulted before the announcement. (<a href='https://www.straitstimes.com/world/europe/In-rare-move-top-Republican-lawmakers-criticize-US-troop-reduction-in-Romania'>The Straits Times</a>)</li></ul><h3>Sources:</h3><ul><li><a href='https://japantoday.com/category/world/the-us-draws-down-troops-on-nato%27s-eastern-flank-as-europe-frets-about-a-security-vacuum'>U.S. reduces troops on NATO&#x27;s eastern flank as Europe frets about security vacuum</a> - japantoday.com</li><li><a href='https://www.nytimes.com/2025/10/29/world/europe/us-troops-eastern-europe-romania.html'>U.S. Says It Will Cut Troops in Eastern Europe</a> - nytimes.com</li><li><a href='https://www.lemonde.fr/en/international/article/2025/10/29/us-to-pull-some-troops-from-eastern-europe_6746899_4.html'>US to pull some troops from Eastern Europe</a> - lemonde.fr</li><li><a href='https://www.washingtonpost.com/world/2025/10/29/romania-nato-us-troops-withdrawal/'>U.S. to withdraw some troops from Romania, NATO’s eastern flank</a> - washingtonpost.com</li><li><a href='https://foreignpolicy.com/2025/10/29/us-troop-withdrawal-europe-romania-russia-ukraine/'>The U.S. Is Withdrawing Some Troops From Eastern Europe</a> - foreignpolicy.com</li><li><a href='https://www.straitstimes.com/world/europe/In-rare-move-top-Republican-lawmakers-criticize-US-troop-reduction-in-Romania'>In rare move, t